      "pos": [
        2424,
        2476
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you want to use a VHDX-format disk in Azure, convert it by using Hyper-V Manager or the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>convert-VHD<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=393656)</ept> cmdlet.",
      "pos": [
        2477,
        2638
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After you do that, use <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Add-AzureVHD<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn495173.aspx)</ept> cmdlet (in Service Management mode) to upload the VHD to a storage account in Azure so you can use it with virtual machines.",
      "pos": [
        2639,
        2857
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The cmdlet converts a dynamic VHD to a fixed VHD, but doesn’t convert from VHDX to VHD.",
      "pos": [
