      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For the Linux images, if you use the Management Portal, ‘azureuser’ is given as a default user name, but you can change this by using ‘From Gallery’ instead of ‘Quick Create’ as the way to create the virtual machine.",
      "pos": [
        9132,
        9348
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using ‘From Gallery’ also lets you decide whether to use a password, an SSH key, or both to log you in.",
      "pos": [
        9349,
        9452
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The user account is a non-privileged user that has ‘sudo’ access to run privileged commands.",
      "pos": [
        9453,
        9545
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The ‘root’ account is disabled.",
      "pos": [
